%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnnals%20of%20Internal%20Medicine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20followed%20more%20than%2036%2C280%20postmenopausal%20women%20who'd%20been%20randomly%20assigned%20to%20either%20take%20vitamin%20D%20and%20calcium%20or%20(unknowingly)%20get%20a%20placebo%20pill%20instead%2C%20for%20a%20period%20of%20about%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20those%20supplements%20seemed%20to%20have%20a%20small%2C%20but%20measurable%20effect%20on%20reducing%20cancer%20deaths.%20But%20taking%20the%20supplements%20didn't%20come%20without%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESignificantly%20less%20breast%20and%20colon%20cancer%20in%20supplement-takers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22caltrate%20vitamin%20d%20plus%20calcium%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef506e6080194819feb69c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221575%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EManufacturers%20often%20sell%20calcium%20and%20vitamin%20D%20in%20a%20single%2C%20combined%20supplement%20for%20bone%20health.%3Cp%3EKaren%20Desjardin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2022%20years%2C%20when%20researchers%20looked%20back%20at%20how%20the%20supplement-takers%20did%20over%20time%20compared%20to%20the%20non-supplementing%20study%20participants%2C%20they%20found%20a%207%25%20reduction%20in%20cancer-related%20deaths%20among%20women%20who%20took%20vitamin%20D%20and%20calcium%20supplements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reductions%20were%20especially%20impressive%20for%20invasive%20breast%20cancer%20(19%25)%2C%20and%20colorectal%20cancer%20(31%25)%2C%20like%20what%20Thomson%20once%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20news%20wasn't%20all%20good.%20Women%20in%20the%20study%20who%20took%20the%20two%20supplements%20together%20also%20had%20a%20modest%20but%20measurable%206%25%20increased%20risk%20of%20developing%20cardiovascular%20diseases%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-causes-a-heart-attack-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheart%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20death%20for%20both%20men%20and%20women%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomson's%20team%20doesn't%20know%20for%20sure%20exactly%20what's%20behind%20that%20increase%2C%20but%20they%20suspect%20the%20difference%20may%20have%20been%20caused%20by%20the%20calcium%20supplements%20encouraging%20some%20more%20calcification%20of%20coronary%20arteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20want%20cardiologists%20to%20say%20'no%20one%20should%20be%20taking%20calcium%20supplements%2C'%20or%20for%20oncologists%20to%20say%20'everyone%20should%20be%20taking%20them'%20%E2%80%94%20we%20really%20need%20to%20look%20at%20individual%20profiles%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20where%20we're%20going%20in%20medicine.%20It's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20one-size-fits-all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20potential%20heart%20risks%2C%20Thomson%20still%20takes%20her%20vitamin%20D%20and%20calcium%20supplements%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupplements-peter-attia-takes-longevity-anti-aging-magnesium-vitamin-d-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyou%20shouldn't%20just%20copy%3C%2Fa%3E%20her%20regimen.%20Instead%2C%20considering%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-supplements-for-longevity-and-anti-aging-expert-recommendations-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupplements%20to%20take%20for%20longevity%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20a%20highly%20personalized%20science.%20Here%20are%20the%20three%20factors%20that%20helped%20inform%20her%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20blood%20test%20results%20to%20determine%20your%20supplement%20regimen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22blood%20test%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef5218ce7f1785b2e88b1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThomson%20says%20she%20considered%20at%20least%20three%20separate%20factors%20before%20incorporating%20vitamin%20D%20and%20calcium%20supplements%20into%20her%20diet%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noticed%20that%20blood%20test%20results%20from%20her%20doctor's%20office%20showed%20her%20vitamin%20D%20levels%20were%20low.%20Taking%20400%20IU%20per%20day%20helped%20get%20her%20into%20the%20normal%20range%20on%20subsequent%20tests%2C%20a%20sign%20her%20strategy%20is%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20suspected%20her%20diet%2C%20as%20a%20vegan-leaning%20%26quot%3Bmeat%20avoider%26quot%3B%20who%20gets%20some%20amount%20of%20calcium%20from%20foods%20like%20tofu%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20salmon%2C%20may%20be%20just%20a%20tad%20low%20on%20calcium.%20(You%20can't%20properly%20measure%20calcium%20levels%20via%20blood%20tests%2C%20since%20the%20body%20tends%20to%20tightly%20regulate%20this%20system%20by%20pulling%20calcium%20from%20our%20muscles%20if%20it's%20not%20getting%20enough%20in%20food.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20she's%20more%20worried%20about%20her%20personal%20history%20of%20colorectal%20cancer%20than%20any%20risk%20of%20calcifying%20her%20coronary%20arteries.%20Her%20calculation%20might've%20been%20different%20if%20she%20had%20a%20personal%20or%20family%20history%20of%20kidney%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThink%20of%20supplements%20as%20an%20addition%20to%20your%20diet%2C%20not%20a%20shortcut%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221056%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mediterranean%20diet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef538cce7f1785b2e88bd0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22842%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAnjelika%20Gretskaia%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThomson%2C%20like%20other%20leading%20researchers%2C%20says%20if%20you%20really%20want%20to%20have%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20your%20risk%20of%20developing%20chronic%20diseases%20like%20cancer%2C%20then%20first%20and%20foremost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanti-aging-foods-brain-heart-health-better-immunity-longevity-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeat%20a%20diverse%20and%20healthy%20diet%20rich%20in%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20whole%20grains%2C%20and%20nuts.%20This%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floma-linda-blue-zone-longevity-secrets-of-seventh-day-adventists-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esame%20strategy%20long-lived%20people%20around%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSupplements%20are%20just%20that%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20intended%20to%20%3Cem%3Esupplement%3C%2Fem%3E%20inadequacies%20in%20a%20diet%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomson%20knows%20that%20supplements%20will%20never%20erase%20a%20person's%20cancer%20risk.%20Any%20health%20benefit%20they%20may%20have%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20slow%2C%20marginal%2C%20and%20specific%20to%20each%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20they%20act%20in%20you%20or%20me%20might%20even%20vary%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20it's%20really%20an%20argument%20for%20looking%20at%20the%20whole%20patient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvitamin-d-calcium-supplements-good-for-aging-reduce-cancer-risk-study-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710190861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef53e590413ab8e1db7901%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busi