Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Jackson%2C%20seasonal%20color%20theory%20is%20inspired%20by%20studies%20from%20the%20German%20colorist%20and%20artist%20Johannes%20Itten.%20His%20studies%20were%20later%20adapted%20for%20fashion%20purposes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Jackson's%20book%2C%20she%20said%20knowing%20your%20season%20and%20wearing%20the%20colors%20within%20it%20can%20help%20you%20look%20better%2C%20shop%20easier%2C%20and%20feel%20more%20excited%20about%20your%20appearance.%20She%20said%20wearing%20the%20right%20colors%20for%20her%20season%20gave%20her%20a%20ton%20of%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20book%20use%20dated%20language%20surrounding%20gender%20and%20race.%C2%A0Many%20of%20the%20examples%20also%20seemed%20to%20be%20specifically%20aimed%20at%20white%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20gave%20up%20on%20the%20TikTok%20effect%20and%20tried%20Jackson's%20online%20quiz%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20was%20really%20dated%20%E2%80%94%20then%20photo-analyzing%20technology.%20I%20still%20couldn't%20figure%20out%20my%20season.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22womens%20photos%20with%20their%20seasons%20on%20Carole%20Jackson's%20website%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62e92bc557dd3c0018dc0046%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22741%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20quiz%20based%20on%20Jackson's%20book%20only%20showed%20examples%20of%20white%20women%20%E2%80%94%20not%20very%20helpful%20to%20people%20of%20color.%3Cp%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fcarolejacksoncolors.com%2F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20attempt%20to%20find%20my%20season%2C%20I%20turned%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarolejacksoncolors.com%2Ftake-the-test%2F%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarolejacksoncolors.com%2Ftake-the-test%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Etest%20on%20Jackson's%20site%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20my%20results%20were%20inconclusive%20and%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20about%20the%20methodology.%20I%20also%20don't%20think%20it%20would%20be%20useful%20for%20people%20of%20color%20to%20only%20see%20examples%20of%20white%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20question%20asked%20of%20me%20was%20which%20%26quot%3Bcolors%20you%20get%20the%20most%20compliments%20on%20when%20you%20wear%20them.%26quot%3B%20But%20this%20was%20tricky%3A%20How%20could%20I%20be%20complimented%20on%20colors%20I%20never%20wear%3F%20Obviously%2C%20I'd%20mostly%20be%20complimented%20on%20wearing%20black%20if%20I%20usually%20wear%20black.%20So%20I%20ended%20up%20choosing%20winter%20colors%2C%20like%20emerald%20and%20black.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20another%20approach%2C%20I%20tried%20the%20site%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcolorwise.me%2F%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcolorwise.me%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EColorwise.me%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20promised%20to%20let%20me%20color%20analyze%20myself%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20PRO%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20after%20an%20hour%20of%20analyzing%20dozens%20of%20photos%20of%20myself%2C%20I%20was%20still%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20results%20ranged%20from%20%26quot%3Bcool%20winter%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20autumn%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20summer.%26quot%3B%20One%20result%20told%20me%20to%20avoid%20black%3B%20the%20next%20said%20it%20was%20one%20of%20my%20best%20colors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20assumed%20I%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bwinter.%26quot%3B%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22celebrities%20winter%20color%20seasons%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63092fb2d266820019ff45b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221172%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELucy%