n%3EAs%20Chitralekha%20Zutshi%20observes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fkashmirs-contested-pasts-9780199481347%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20her%20book%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EContested%20Pasts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Persian%20texts%20are%20not%20only%20dialogically%20connected%20with%20its%20Sanskrit%20histories%2C%20but%20also%20carry%20their%20unique%20imprint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20irony%20of%20%E2%80%98decolonisation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%2C%20however%2C%20the%20colonial%20historiography%20led%20by%20European%20scholars%20such%20as%20H.H.%20Wilson%20and%20Georg%20B%C3%BChler%20that%20accelerated%20the%20periodisation%20of%20Kashmiri%20history%20into%20the%20categories%20of%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim.%20It%20had%20the%20effect%20of%20deracinating%20the%20Sanskrit%20texts%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERajatarangini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVishnudharmottara%20Purana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20localised%20context%2C%20suturing%20them%20to%20notions%20of%20an%20overriding%20Hindu%20antiquity%20that%20bound%20Kashmir%20with%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20refashioning%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERajatarangini%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20expression%20of%20Indic%20civilisational%20spirit%2C%20Zutshi%20argues%2C%20elided%20its%20place%20within%20the%20Persian%20historical%20tradition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEventually%2C%20the%20Persian%20historical%20tradition%20declined%20and%20the%20manuscripts%20were%20scavenged%20to%20fish%20out%20anecdotes%20that%20appeared%20to%20re-inscribe%20what%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FThe-Syncretic-Traditions-of-Islamic-Religious-Architecture-of-Kashmir-Early%2FHamdani%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367744298