3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%2028th%20we%20were%20taken%20to%20the%20Ryazan%20military%20camp%20where%20our%20passports%20were%20taken%20away%20by%20the%20army%20officials.%20They%20communicated%20with%20us%20using%20Google%20translate%20and%20told%20us%20to%20rest%20for%20a%20few%20days%20%E2%80%98until%20our%20turn%20comes%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20ready%20to%20start%20our%20new%20job%20and%20enquired%20about%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20role%20of%20a%20helper.%20The%20army%20officer%20was%20surprised%20at%20the%20question%20and%20said%20that%20there%20are%20no%20helper%20jobs%20there.%20He%20only%20told%20us%20that%20we%20would%20be%20readied%20and%20then%20taken%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20confusion%20prevailed%20and%20soon%20we%20saw%20the%20arrival%20of%20heavily%20injured%20men%20in%20the%20camp.%20Some%20had%20lost%20their%20arm%2C%20leg%20and%20some%20had%20lost%20their%20fingers.%20They%20looked%20like%20war%20wounds.%20I%20thought%20that%20I%20might%20have%20been%20employed%20to%20serve%20these%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20speaking%20to%20some%20of%20the%20injured%20men.%20But%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20tell%20us%20anything.%20Looked%20like%20they%20had%20strict%20instructions%20to%20not%20speak%20to%20the%20newcomers%20in%20the%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20go%20there%2C%20you%20will%20get%20to%20know%20everything%2C%E2%80%9D%20murmured%20an%20injured%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20passing%20day%2C%20the%20suspense%20kept%20building%20up%20and%20I%20was%20perplexed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%20a%20man%20from%20Kazakhstan%20told%20us%20that%20the%20contract%20we%20had%20signed%20was%20in%20fact%20an%20agreement%20to%20join%20the%20Russian%20army%20as%20a%20fighter%20in%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20information%20sent%20chills%20down%20my%20spine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20us%20were%20so%20shocked%20and%20scared%20that%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99