pless%20nights%2C%20haunted%20by%20the%20memories%20of%20Hamil%20and%20other%20men%20who%20were%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20wonder%20how%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamil%20wanted%20me%20to%20get%20back%20to%20India%20and%20try%20to%20rescue%20him%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20help.%20But%20it%20was%20too%20late.%20He%20died%20before%20I%20could%20do%20anything%20to%20rescue%20him.%20The%20regret%20won%E2%80%99t%20let%20me%20be%20at%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20plead%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20the%20scammers%20and%20rescue%20our%20men%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20Time%20is%20running%20out.%20Every%20single%20day%20at%20the%20frontline%20is%20a%20call%20for%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20told%20to%20Shalu%20Yadav.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710153019000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11115218%2FFeatured-image.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsmuggled-into-russia-i-escaped-the-death-trap-laid-by-a-travel-agent%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20went%20straight%20to%20the%20Indian%20embassy%20in%20Moscow%20%5Bon%20my%20escape%5D%20and%20shared%20details%20of%20the%20scam%20with%20the%20embassy%20officials.%20To%20my%20surprise%2C%20the%20embassy%20official%20told%20me%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Russian%20Army%20to%20avoid%20punishment%20as%20I%20had%20signed%20a%20contract%20with%20them.%20He%20assured%20me%20that%20he%20will%20work%20on%20our%20case%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20give%20them%20a%20month%20or%20so.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsmuggled-into-russia-i-escaped-the-death-trap-laid-by-a-travel-agent%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Very%20Well%20Reasoned'%3A%20SC%20Refuses%20to%20Stay%20Bombay%20HC%20Order%20Acquitting%20Saibaba%2C%20Others%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07181050%2Fimage-1914.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%20(March%2011)%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20judgment%20acquitting%20former%20Delhi%20University%20professor%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20and%20five%20others%20in%20a%20UAPA%20case%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20is%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20well%20reasoned%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-gn-saibaba-alleged-maoist-links-case-uapa-state-of-maharashtra-251834%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Sandeep%20Mehta%20were%20hearing%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20state%20of%20Maharashtra.%20The%20bench%20pointed%20out%20that%20Saibaba%20had%20his%20co-accused%20had%20been%20acquitted%20twice%2C%20by%20two%20different%20benches%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20told%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20S.V.%20Raju%2C%20appearing%20for%20Maharashtra%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20two%20orders%20of%20acquittal%20by%20two%20different%20benches.%C2%A0%3Ci%3EPrima%20facie%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20we%20find%20that%20the%20judgment%20is%20very%20well-reasoned.%20Since%20on%20an%20earlier%20occasion%2C%20this%20court%20had%20interfered%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20honour%20that.%20Otherwise%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20well-reasoned%20judgment%20by%20the%20high%20court.%20In%20ordinary%20course%2C%20we%20would%20not%20have%20entertained%20this%20appeal.%20The%20parameters%20of%20interference%20with%20acquittal%20orders%20are%20very%20limited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20hard-earned%20acquittal.%20How%20many%20years%20has%20the%20man%20spent%20in%20jail%3F%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Mehta%20added%2C%20followed%20by%20Justice%20Gavai%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20law%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20presumption%20of%20innocence.%20Once%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20order%20of%20acquittal%2C%20that%20presumption%20gets%20fortified.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsaibaba-acquittal-from-lack-of-sanction-to-dodgy-evidence-high-court-judgment-tears-into-states-case%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20judgment%20had%20criticised%20both%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20probe%20and%20the%20trial%20court%20judgment%20finding%20the%20men%20guilty.%20Justice%20Vinay%20G.%20Joshi%20and%20Justice%20Valimiki%20S.%20Menezes%20on%20March%205%20acquitted%20Saibaba%2C%20along%20with%20journalist%20Prashant%20Rahi%2C%20Mahesh%20Tikri%2C%20Hem%20Keshwdatta%20Mishra%20and%20Vijay%20Nan%20Tikri%20of%20all%20charges.%20The%20sixth%20person%20in%20the%20case%2C%20Pandu%20Narote%2C%20died%20in%20August%202022%2C%20awaiting%20this%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaibaba%2C%20who%20is%20wheelchair-bound%20and%20is%20over%2090%25%20handicapped%2C%20said%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20move%20an%20inch%20without%20others%E2%80%99%20help.%20He%20said%20after%20his%20release%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fit-is-only-by-chance-that-i-came-out-of-prison-alive-g-n-saibaba%5C%22%3Eonly%20by%20chance%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20that%20he%20is%20coming%20out%20of%20jail%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20in%20two%20years%20that%20the%20Nagpur%20bench%20has%20acquitted%20Saibaba%20and%20others.%20On%20October%2014%2C%202022%2C%20the%20same%20court%2C%20comprising%20of%20Justice%20Rohit%20B.%20Deo%20and%20Anil%20Pansare%20had%20overturned%20the%20Gadchiroli%20session%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgement.%20Barring%20Vijay%20Tikri%2C%20who%20was%20convicted%20to%20ten%20years%20rigorous%20punishment%2C%20the%20others%20were%20awarded%20life%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20discharging%20all%20five%20accused%2C%20Justice%20Deo%20had%20observed%20that%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%20cannot%20be%20sacrificed%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20%E2%80%9Cperceived%20peril%20to%20national%20security%E2%80%9D.%20The%20bench%20directed%20the%20convicts%20to%20be%20released%20forthwith%20from%20jail%20unless%20they%20are%20accused%20in%20any%20other%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defence%20lawyers%20appearing%20for%20Saibaba%20and%20others%20had%20challenged%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20sanction%20order%20issued%20to%20prosecute%20under%20the%20stringent%20provisions%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%20They%20had%20relied%20on%20Section%2041%20(A)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20which%20clearly%20states%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20court%20shall%20take%20cognizance%20of%20any%20offence%20without%20the%20previous%20sanction%20of%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20any%20officer%20authorised%20by%20the%20Central%20Government%20on%20this%20behalf%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20in%202022%20had%20called%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20valid%20sanction%20order%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbad%20in%20law%20and%20invalid%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20the%20Nagpur%20central%20jail%20authorities%20had%20refused%20to%20release%20them%20immediately%20and%20meanwhile%2C%20the%20state%20government%20had%20rushed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20stay%20on%20the%20order%2C%20and%20had%20received%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710151218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07181050%2Fimage-1914.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvery-well-reasoned-sc-refuses-to-stay-bombay-hc-order-acquitting-saibaba-others%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20hard-earned%20acquittal.%20How%20many%20years%20has%20the%20man%20spent%20in%20jail%3F%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Mehta%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvery-well-reasoned-sc-refuses-to-stay-bombay-hc-order-acquitting-saibaba-others%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PMO%2C%20VIP%20References%20Can%20Now%20Be%20Considered%20For%20Quick%20Disposal%20of%20Income%20Tax%20Appeals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F24135657%2Fcash-india.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Income%20tax%20officials%20may%20now%20consider%20references%20from%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20(PMO)%20or%20from%20very%20important%20persons%20(VIPs)%20when%20choosing%20to%20dispose%20of%20appeals%20on%20a%20priority%20or%20out-of-turn%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%20said%20this%20while%20issuing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20240309111128%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fcbdt-526938.pdf%5C%22%3Efresh%20and%20superseding%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20when%20senior%20officials%20can%20choose%20to%20expedite%20the%20disposal%20of%20income%20tax%20appeals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20guidelines%2C%20there%20are%20five%20situations%20where%20appeals%20at%20a%20certain%20organisation%20level%20may%20be%20expeditiously%20disposed%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20when%20a%20case%20involves%20a%20demand%20higher%20than%20Rs%201%20crore%2C%20when%20VIPs%20or%20the%20PMO%20refers%20a%20case%2C%20when%20directions%20are%20received%20from%20a%20court%2C%20when%20senior%20citizens%20make%20requests%20or%20when%20a%20case%20involves%20genuine%20hardship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxguru.in%2Fincome-tax%2Fguidelines-priority-turn-disposal-appeals-csit-au-csit-appeals.html%5C%22%3EPrevious%20guidelines%20issued%20in%20December%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20mentioned%20five%20situations%20but%20VIP%20or%20PMO%20references%20were%20not%20one%20of%20them.%20Instead%2C%20they%20contained%20a%20provision%20for%20expeditious%20disposal%20where%20refunds%20were%20higher%20than%20Rs%201%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20guidelines%2C%20issued%20on%20Thursday%20(March%207)%2C%20deal%20with%20appeals%20pending%20at%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Income%20Tax%20(Appeal%2FAppeal%20Unit)%20and%20Additional%20or%20Joint%20Commissioner%20of%20Income%20Tax%20(Appeal)%20organisational%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20that%20requests%20for%20expeditious%20disposal%20that%20are%20either%20raised%20at%20the%20appellant%E2%80%99s%20instance%2C%20or%20are%20referred%20by%20an%20assessing%20officer%20or%20a%20range%20head%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20considered%E2%80%9D%20by%20Principal%20Commissioners%2C%20Chief%20Commissioners%20or%20Directors%20General%20of%20Income%20Tax%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20recommendations%20made%20by%20jurisdictional%20principal%20income%20tax%20commissioners%20among%20other%20ranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20appeals%20within%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20faceless%20income%20tax%20appeals%20commissioners%20are%20concerned%2C%20the%20new%20guidelines%20say%20that%20requests%20for%20expeditious%20disposals%20shall%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20Principal%20Chief%20Commissioner%20of%20Income%20Tax%20(National%20Faceless%20Appeal%20Centre).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnarendra-modi-launches-new-transparent-taxation-platform-faceless%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98faceless%E2%80%99%20income%20tax%20assessment%20and%20appeals%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20created%20in%202020%20so%20that%20taxpayers%20would%20not%20have%20to%20physically%20visit%20income%20tax%20offices%20or%20meet%20officials%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20intended%20to%20increase%20convenience%20for%20taxpayers%20and%20rein%20in%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710150640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F24135657%2Fcash-india.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpmo-vip-references-expeditious-income-tax-appeal-disposal-cbdt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%20said%20this%20while%20issuing%20fresh%20and%20superseding%20guidelines%20last%20week%20on%20when%20senior%20officials%20can%20choose%20to%20expedite%20the%20disposal%20of%20income%20tax%20appeals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpmo-vip-references-expeditious-income-tax-appeal-disposal-cbdt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ian%20Chappell%20criticizes%20Ben%20Stokes'%20captaincy%20in%20India%20series%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710150179000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108392318%2Cimgsize-32476.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fengland-in-india%2Fhe-gave-the-ball-to-a-ian-chappell-criticizes-ben-stokes-captaincy-in-india-series%2Farticleshow%2F108392205.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Australia%20captain%20Ian%20Chappell%20has%20criticized%20England%20captain%20Ben%20Stokes%20for%20a%20critical%20lapse%20in%20strategy%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20Stokes'%20decision%20to%20use%20part-time%20spinner%20Joe%20Root%20instead%20of%20experienced%20Jimmy%20Anderson%20in%20the%20fourth%20Test%20at%20Ranchi%20allowed%20India%20to%20gain%20momentum%20and%20shift%20the%20match's%20balance%20in%20their%20favor%2C%20ultimately%20leading%20to%20India's%20series-sealing%20victory.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22North%20Kore